ety even with those liberal intellectuals who were his primary opponents. The book also sets Mills firmly within the history of American sociology and traces his political trajectory from committed supporter of the Old Left labor movement to influential herald of an international New Left. More than just a biography, Radical Ambition illuminates the career of a brilliant thinker whose life and works illustrate both the promise and the dilemmas of left-wing social thought in the United States.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aSociologyzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh  a1950s.  a20th century.  aamerica.  aamerican culture.  aamerican politics.  aamerican socialism.  aamerican sociology.  aamerican studies.  abiography.  ac wright mills.  aintellectual thinkers.  ainternational politics.  alabor movement.  aleft wing thought.  aliberal intellectuals.  anew left.  anonfiction.  aold left.  apolitical left.  apolitical outsiders.  apolitics.  aradical politics.  aradical socialism.  aradicalism and revolution.  arebellion.  aretrospective.  asocial critics.  asocial thought.  asociologists.  aunited states.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052025836540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094344540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520943445423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520943445/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY